    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Those who study or practice the science of human and animal mind and behavior, both healthy and unhealthy, with the focus on individuals in interaction with their environment. For those who deal with the treatment of mental, emotional, and behavioral disorders, use "psychiatrists."</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Aquellos que estudian o ejercen la ciencia mental y de comportamiento humano y animal, tanto sanos como enfermos, con un interés en la reacción de individuos con su medioambiente. Para aquellos que se ocupan con tratamientos mentales, emocionales y de desórdenes conductuales, use "psiquiatra".</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Zij die psychologie bestuderen of in de praktijk beoefenen, de wetenschap van de geest en het gedrag van mens en dier, zowel gezond als ongezond, waarbij het accent ligt op individuen in relatie tot hun omgeving. Gebruik 'psychiaters' voor hen die zich bezighouden met het behandelen van gedragsstoornissen en mentale of emotionele stoornissen.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>研究或從事人類與動物的心智行為的專家，包含健康與不健康的研究對象、特別是個人與環境間的互動。若是指治療心理、情緒、以及行為偏差的專家，則為「精神科醫師」(psychiatrists)。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
